<span id="freeTextContainer5546310512986567675">I was criticized for giving this five stars before it came out :) Which I suppose I can understand since it slightly affects the average score.<br/><br/>Well, I&apos;ve read it now and Sanderson did not disappoint. I loved the final volume of this super-epic, even though getting to the end was bittersweet.<br/><br/>To review this book is to review the entire series. The bottom line is that while it has some low points (Crossroads of Twilight), even those have some pretty neat moments. I always cheered when I heard the b</span>
  <span id="freeText5546310512986567675" style="display:none">I was criticized for giving this five stars before it came out :) Which I suppose I can understand since it slightly affects the average score.<br /><br />Well, I've read it now and Sanderson did not disappoint. I loved the final volume of this super-epic, even though getting to the end was bittersweet.<br /><br />To review this book is to review the entire series. The bottom line is that while it has some low points (Crossroads of Twilight), even those have some pretty neat moments. I always cheered when I heard the book count was going UP, because I loved immersing myself in Robert Jordan's world.<br /><br />When Sanderson picks up the reigns in The Gathering Storm, the pace picks up dramatically and the more tiresome subplots are wrapped up very quickly.<br /><br /><br /></span>
