<div id="review_1084005998" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1084005998" />
    <a title="Lisa" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/33359750-lisa"><img alt="Lisa" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1576550045p2/33359750.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1084005998?book_show_action=true">Oct 19, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lisa" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lisa" href="/user/show/33359750-lisa">Lisa</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1084005998" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3292237643063951265">I have loved this series. Every single word. Some people claim it&apos;s all too much. No, the world building is actually remarkable. Characters?.Yes. From 14 books ago until now. Yes. <br/>Honestly? I love these books so much that I&apos;m left speechless. Nothing.<br/>There isn&apos;t anything that will convince another to read this.<br/>Hell, in truth I will akways, and have always believed that Sanderson effed this story up! Maybe not the ending. He did his best to follow what Jordan wrote. <br/>What I think Sanderson missed </span>
  <span id="freeText3292237643063951265" style="display:none">I have loved this series. Every single word. Some people claim it's all too much. No, the world building is actually remarkable. Characters?.Yes. From 14 books ago until now. Yes. <br />Honestly? I love these books so much that I'm left speechless. Nothing.<br />There isn't anything that will convince another to read this.<br />Hell, in truth I will akways, and have always believed that Sanderson effed this story up! Maybe not the ending. He did his best to follow what Jordan wrote. <br />What I think Sanderson missed was the heart. <br />The one who actually died to save the world was but a footnote. Some more few died. Some that we loved, and their deaths weren't even acknowledged. <br />Even discounting the dead. Mats humor wasn't humorous. <br />The sword stances had completely changed, and in the end it turned out that I was thankful that Brandon Sanderson had completed this series. Even though May completely lost his sense of humor! "Have I already said that?" I'd totally say it again!!<br />Crikey! Honestly? I love Jordan. Sanderson effed this up! Changing my review from 5 to 3. Give it a few years, and I may send Sanderson a letter with frown lines! Lol!<br />Mostly, I was bothered about how Sanderson skewed Mats humor. No one was funny. Tried, but no.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3292237643063951265" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
